  "prompt": "Are there laws that prevent the disguise of illicit funds?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have anti-money laundering (AML) laws designed to prevent the disguising or concealing of illicit funds. Key examples include:\n\n1. Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n2. Money Laundering Control Act\n3. Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n4. FATF (Financial Action Task Force) international standards\n5. European Union Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n\nThese laws require financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n\nViolations can result in significant legal penalties and criminal prosecution.",
